Decodes a numeric &quot;leaf&quot; value.

These are integer literals encountered in the type stream. If the value is positive and less than LF&#95;NUMERIC (1 &lt;&lt; 15), it is emitted directly in Data. Otherwise, it has a tag like LF&#95;CHAR that indicates the bitwidth and sign of the numeric data.

### mergeIdRecords() {#a56089b6df59b900fd953910dccb91612}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Error llvm::codeview::mergeIdRecords (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/codeview/mergingtypetablebuilder">MergingTypeTableBuilder</a> &amp; Dest, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/arrayref">ArrayRef</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/codeview/typeindex">TypeIndex</a> &gt; Types, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/codeview/typeindex">TypeIndex</a> &gt; &amp; SourceToDest, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="#a3b5a871028c3a00c356376368d4d57d9">CVTypeArray</a> &amp; Ids)</>}>
Merge one set of id records into another.

This method assumes that all records are id records, and there are no <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/type">Type</a> records present. However, since Id records can refer back to <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/type">Type</a> records, this method assumes that the referenced type records have also been merged into another type stream (for example using the above method), and accepts the mapping from source to dest for that stream so that it can re-write the type record mappings accordingly.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="Dest">The table to store the re-written id records into.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Types">The mapping to use for the type records that these id records refer to.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="SourceToDest">A vector, indexed by the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/codeview/typeindex">TypeIndex</a> in the source id stream, that contains the index of the corresponding id record in the destination stream.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Ids">The collection of id records to merge in.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error/#a4dfd0813c3d0e0a30439b5a3e9196b59">Error::success()</a> if the operation succeeded, otherwise an appropriate error code.
</SectionUser>
